LAGOS – For the fifth consecutive month in the year, Nigeria’s inflation closed upward to 22.41 percent from 22.22 percent recorded in April amid the removal of sub­sidy on petrol. This is according to the May inflation data con­tained in the latest Con­sumer Price Index (CPI) report released on Thurs­day by the National Bureau of Statistics (NBS). The CPI measures the rate of change in prices of goods and services.